0of%2059.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d26fdd22-b2df-46b0-acf4-995c00f9be2c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMiddle%20management%20positions%20always%20included%20reasonable%20work%20hours%20compared%20to%20colleagues%20above%20and%20below%20me%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20four%20years%20working%20as%20a%20clerk%20for%20corporate%20law%20firms%2C%20I%20pivoted%20to%20an%20IT%20career%20in%201994%2C%20working%20as%20a%20software%20support%20engineer%20in%20Seattle.%20I%20enjoyed%20working%20on%20a%20new%20operating%20system%20as%20part%20of%20the%20job.%20It%20felt%20more%20like%20a%20fun%20hobby%20than%20actual%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20promoted%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-managers-valuable-company-employee-success-growth-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emiddle%20management%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20performing%20well%20in%20identifying%20and%20resolving%20system%20defects.%20My%20core%20responsibilities%20were%20to%20assist%20and%20train%20junior%20support%20engineers%20and%20track%20their%20ability%20to%20solve%20problems%20for%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20left%20that%20job%20after%20almost%20two%20years%20and%20went%20on%20to%20hold%20several%20other%20middle%20management%20roles%2C%20including%20as%20a%20project%20manager%20and%20applications%20engineer%20at%20startups%20and%20larger%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-manager-hiring-white-collar-recession-layoffs-jobs-efficiency-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMiddle%20management%20positions%3C%2Fa%3E%20always%20came%20with%20reasonable%20work%20hours%20relative%20to%20my%20IT%20colleagues%20above%20and%20below%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoftware%20developers%20typically%20had%20to%20put%20in%20extra%20hours%20to%20complete%20coding%20tasks.%20As%20far%20I%20could%20tell%2C%20the%20management%20teams%20above%20me%20worked%2050%20to%2065%20hours%20a%20week%20to%20oversee%20tea