e%20five%20Grand%20Slams%20without%20winning%20the%20title%20he%20needs%20to%20surpass%20Margaret%20Court's%2024%20and%20become%20the%20all-time%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20failed%20to%20collect%20one%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20seven%20years%20in%202024%20with%20his%20last%20coming%20at%20the%202023%20US%20Open%2C%20casting%20further%20doubt%20on%20whether%20he%20will%20ever%20get%20past%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20defeat%20also%20deprived%20him%20of%20a%20100th%20career%20title.%20Roger%20Federer%20(102)%20is%20the%20only%20player%2C%20man%20or%20woman%2C%20to%20reach%20the%20century%20mark.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZverev's%20reward%20is%20a%20clash%20in%20Sunday's%20showdown%20with%20either%20world%20number%20one%20Jannik%20Sinner%20or%20American%2021st%20seed%20Ben%20Shelton.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20German%20has%20been%20a%20Grand%20Slam%20runner-up%20twice%20before%2C%20at%20last%20year's%20French%20Open%20and%20the%202020%20US%20Open%2C%20he%20has%20never%20before%20been%20to%20the%20final%20in%20Melbourne.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%20at%20the%20same%20semi-final%20stage%20he%20crashed%20to%20Daniil%20Medvedev%20in%20five%20sets%20after%20holding%20a%202-0%20lead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20came%20into%20the%20season%20with%20renewed%20vigour%20after%20ending%202024%20as%20world%20number%20two%2C%20winning%20more%20matches%20than%20anyone%20bar%20Sinner%20and%20back%20to%20his%20best%20after%20a%20horrific%20ankle%20injury.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDjokovic%20came%20into%20the%20clash%20with%20questions%20over%20his%20fitness%20after%20needing%20medical%20attention%20in%20his%20four-set%20quarter-final%20win%20against%20Carlos%20Alcaraz.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20before%20the%20match%20he%20was%20worried%20about%20his%20physical%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20has%20demonstrated%20remarkable%20powers%20of%20recovery%20more%20than%20once%20in%20his%20career%20and%20it%20didn't%20appear%20to%20hinder%20him%20initi